---
import Narrative from '../../layouts/Narrative.astro';
---

<Narrative title="Chapters — ICOS">

  <!-- 1. Hero -->
  <section class="scene ch-hero">
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="col-wide">
        <p class="label ch-tag" data-reveal>ICOS · Local Commons</p>
        <h1 class="ch-headline" data-reveal>
          The commons is<br>
          local by nature.
        </h1>
        <p class="ch-lede" data-reveal>
          A chapter is simply a group of people in a place who have committed
          to maintaining a commons practice over time. It doesn't require
          registration, approval, or permission from us — or from anyone.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 2. What is a chapter? -->
  <section class="ch-section">
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="col-wide">
        <div class="two-col">
          <div class="ch-aside">
            <p class="label aside-label" data-reveal>What Is<br>a Chapter?</p>
          </div>
          <div class="ch-body">
            <h2 data-reveal>Three people, a place, a recurring practice.</h2>
            <p data-reveal>
              A chapter is a group of three or more people in a defined place —
              a block, a neighborhood, a village, a city district — who are running
              at least one commons pattern on a recurring basis.
            </p>
            <p data-reveal>
              It can be as small as one block running a monthly dinner, or as
              large as a city district hosting quarterly repair days and a seasonal
              fire. What makes it a chapter isn't the size. It's the commitment
              to showing up again.
            </p>
            <p data-reveal>
              A chapter might run a monthly feast, a quarterly repair day, a
              biannual story archive session, or a seasonal fire. It doesn't have
              to do everything. It has to do something, consistently, in a place
              that people can find.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="grid"><div class="col-wide"><hr class="ch-rule" /></div></div>

  <!-- 3. How to start one -->
  <section class="ch-section">
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="col-wide">
        <div class="two-col">
          <div class="ch-aside">
            <p class="label aside-label" data-reveal>How to<br>Start One</p>
          </div>
          <div class="ch-body">
            <h2 data-reveal>Start before you're ready.</h2>
            <p data-reveal>
              The only requirement for starting a chapter is that you start.
              Everything else — the name, the structure, the formal registration —
              can come after you've run the thing twice.
            </p>
            <ol class="steps">
              <li data-reveal>
                <span class="step-n label">01</span>
                <div>
                  <strong>Start a pattern</strong>
                  <p>Pick one of the seven commons patterns and run it. Use the <a href="/start-here">Start Here</a> guide for a practical walkthrough. The first gathering doesn't need to be perfect.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li data-reveal>
                <span class="step-n label">02</span>
                <div>
                  <strong>Run it at least twice</strong>
                  <p>A single event is a party. Two gatherings with the same group is the beginning of a practice. The second gathering is when you find out if it has roots.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li data-reveal>
                <span class="step-n label">03</span>
                <div>
                  <strong>Recruit at least one other steward</strong>
                  <p>No one person should hold the commons alone. Find someone who showed up, who cared, who you'd trust with the thing when you can't be there. That's your co-steward.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li data-reveal>
                <span class="step-n label">04</span>
                <div>
                  <strong>Name your circle and your place</strong>
                  <p>Give your chapter a name — something that belongs to your neighborhood, not to ICOS. The name should feel local. Then name the place: the neighborhood, the district, the block. Specificity matters.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li data-reveal>
                <span class="step-n label">05</span>
                <div>
                  <strong>Register here</strong>
                  <p>When you're ready to be listed in the directory and connected with other chapters, register below. Registration is free, takes five minutes, and is entirely optional — the commons doesn't require it.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="grid"><div class="col-wide"><hr class="ch-rule" /></div></div>

  <!-- 4. What chapters get -->
  <section class="ch-section">
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="col-wide">
        <div class="two-col">
          <div class="ch-aside">
            <p class="label aside-label" data-reveal>What<br>You Get</p>
          </div>
          <div class="ch-body">
            <h2 data-reveal>A peer network, not a franchise.</h2>
            <p data-reveal>
              Registering as a chapter connects you to other people doing the
              same work, in different places. It doesn't put you under anyone's
              governance or obligate you to anything beyond running your pattern.
            </p>
            <ul class="benefits">
              <li data-reveal>
                <span class="benefit-marker label">—</span>
                <div>
                  <strong>Peer connection</strong>
                  <p>Access to the network of chapter stewards — people running the same patterns in different cities who can answer the questions that aren't in any guide.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li data-reveal>
                <span class="benefit-marker label">—</span>
                <div>
                  <strong>Pattern support</strong>
                  <p>Implementation notes, governance templates, and evolving documentation drawn from what chapters have actually learned in the field.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li data-reveal>
                <span class="benefit-marker label">—</span>
                <div>
                  <strong>Listing in this directory</strong>
                  <p>When someone in your city searches for a local commons, they find you. That visibility matters for drawing in neighbors who are looking for exactly what you're building.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li data-reveal>
                <span class="benefit-marker label">—</span>
                <div>
                  <strong>Field notes eligibility</strong>
                  <p>Registered chapters can submit dispatches to the <a href="/field-notes">Field Notes</a> — accounts of what's working, what you've learned, what happened that surprised you.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li data-reveal>
                <span class="benefit-marker label">—</span>
                <div>
                  <strong>Governance resources</strong>
                  <p>Access to the deeper governance documentation — stewardship models, conflict frameworks, succession planning — for chapters that are growing and need more structure.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="grid"><div class="col-wide"><hr class="ch-rule" /></div></div>

  <!-- 5. Directory -->
  <section class="ch-section ch-directory-section">
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="col-wide">
        <div class="two-col">
          <div class="ch-aside">
            <p class="label aside-label" data-reveal>The<br>Directory</p>
          </div>
          <div class="ch-body">
            <h2 data-reveal>Chapters, by place.</h2>
            <p data-reveal>
              This directory lists active registered chapters — groups running
              at least one commons pattern on a recurring basis in a specific place.
            </p>
            <div class="directory-empty" data-reveal>
              <div class="directory-empty-inner">
                <p class="label directory-status">No chapters listed yet</p>
                <p class="directory-empty-body">
                  Yours could be first. Every chapter in this directory started
                  with a single gathering and a small group who kept showing up.
                  There is no minimum size. There is no threshold to clear.
                  There is only the commitment to begin.
                </p>
                <a href="mailto:ap@uxtheory.co?subject=Chapter%20Registration%20—%20ICOS&body=Chapter%20name%3A%0APlace%2FNeighborhood%3A%0APattern(s)%20running%3A%0ACadence%3A%0ASteward%20name%3A%0A" class="ch-register-cta label">
                  Register Your Chapter →
                </a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="grid"><div class="col-wide"><hr class="ch-rule" /></div></div>

  <!-- 6. Federated model -->
  <section class="ch-section ch-federated">
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="col-wide">
        <div class="two-col">
          <div class="ch-aside">
            <p class="label aside-label" data-reveal>How It<br>Works</p>
          </div>
          <div class="ch-body">
            <h2 data-reveal>Federated, not franchised.</h2>
            <p data-reveal>
              Chapters are autonomous. They belong to their place and their
              people. ICOS provides the pattern language and the peer network —
              not governance, not oversight, not the right to tell you how to
              run your table.
            </p>
            <p data-reveal>
              This is intentional. A commons that depends on a central organization
              is fragile. A network of autonomous, locally-rooted chapters is
              resilient. When one chapter goes dormant, others continue. When a
              new chapter forms, it draws on the accumulated knowledge of the
              whole — but answers only to its own people.
            </p>
            <blockquote class="ch-blockquote" data-reveal>
              We offer the pattern. You own the practice.
              The commons belongs to the place where it lives.
            </blockquote>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Closing CTA -->
  <section class="scene ch-closing">
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="col-center">
        <p class="label" data-reveal>Ready to begin?</p>
        <h2 class="ch-closing-h" data-reveal>
          Start with one gathering.<br>
          See what grows.
        </h2>
        <p class="ch-closing-sub" data-reveal>
          You don't need to register to run a commons. But when you're ready
          to connect with others doing the same work, we'll be here.
        </p>
        <nav class="ch-ctas" data-reveal>
          <a href="/start-here" class="ch-cta-main">Read the Start Here Guide →</a>
          <a href="/patterns" class="ch-cta-sub">Explore the Commons Patterns</a>
        </nav>
        <p class="label ch-closing-mark" data-reveal>Chapters · ICOS · Commons Operating System</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Narrative>

<style>
  /* ── Hero ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */

  .ch-hero {
    padding-top: 100px;
    min-height: 0;
    align-items: flex-start;
    padding-bottom: 48px;
  }

  .ch-tag {
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .ch-headline {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(40px, 5.5vw, 76px);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.08;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin: 0 0 28px;
    max-width: 22ch;
  }

  .ch-lede {
    font-size: clamp(17px, 1.8vw, 21px);
    line-height: 1.55;
    max-width: 52ch;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── Sections ───────────────────────────────────────────────────── */

  .ch-section {
    padding: 56px 0;
  }

  .ch-rule {
    border: 0;
    border-top: 0.5px solid var(--rule);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── Two-col layout ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */

  .two-col {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr;
    gap: 32px;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .aside-label {
    line-height: 1.8;
    padding-top: 6px;
  }

  /* ── Body prose ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── */

  .ch-body h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(26px, 3vw, 40px);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.2;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    margin: 0 0 28px;
  }

  .ch-body p {
    margin: 0 0 20px;
    max-width: 58ch;
  }

  /* ── Steps ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */

  .steps {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 32px 0 0;
  }

  .steps li {
    display: flex;
    gap: 24px;
    padding: 24px 0;
    border-top: 0.5px solid var(--rule);
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .step-n {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    padding-top: 3px;
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .steps strong {
    display: block;
    font-size: 19px;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }

  .steps p {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 44ch;
  }

  /* ── Benefits list ──────────────────────────────────────────────── */

  .benefits {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 28px 0 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
    border-top: 0.5px solid var(--rule);
  }

  .benefits li {
    display: flex;
    gap: 16px;
    padding: 20px 0;
    border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--rule);
    align-items: flex-start;
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .benefit-marker {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    color: var(--accent);
    padding-top: 3px;
  }

  .benefits strong {
    display: block;
    font-size: 17px;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }

  .benefits p {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 50ch;
  }

  /* ── Directory ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── */

  .ch-directory-section {
    padding-top: 56px;
  }

  .directory-empty {
    margin-top: 32px;
  }

  .directory-empty-inner {
    border: 0.5px solid var(--rule);
    border-radius: 2px;
    padding: 48px;
    text-align: center;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--paper) 97%, var(--ink) 3%);
  }

  .directory-status {
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .directory-empty-body {
    font-size: clamp(16px, 1.5vw, 18px);
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--ink);
    max-width: 44ch;
    margin: 0 auto 28px;
  }

  .ch-register-cta {
    display: inline-block;
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    border: 0.5px solid var(--accent);
    padding: 12px 24px;
    transition: background 0.15s, color 0.15s;
  }
  .ch-register-cta:hover {
    background: var(--accent);
    color: var(--paper);
  }

  /* ── Blockquote ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── */

  .ch-blockquote {
    border-left: 2px solid var(--accent);
    padding-left: 24px;
    margin: 36px 0 0;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(17px, 1.8vw, 21px);
    line-height: 1.5;
    max-width: 48ch;
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  /* ── Closing ────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */

  .ch-closing {
    text-align: center;
    min-height: 0;
    padding: 80px 0;
  }

  .ch-closing-h {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(30px, 4.5vw, 58px);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin: 12px 0 20px;
  }

  .ch-closing-sub {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 20px;
    margin: 0 auto 36px;
    max-width: 46ch;
  }

  .ch-ctas {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 14px;
  }

  .ch-cta-main {
    font-size: 20px;
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration-color: transparent;
    transition: text-decoration-color 0.2s;
  }
  .ch-cta-main:hover { text-decoration-color: var(--accent); }

  .ch-cta-sub {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--fs-label);
    letter-spacing: var(--fs-label-tracking);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .ch-cta-sub:hover { color: var(--ink); }

  .ch-closing-mark {
    display: block;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-top: 48px;
  }

  /* ── Responsive ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── */

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .two-col {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    .aside-label {
      margin-bottom: 4px;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }
    .directory-empty-inner {
      padding: 32px 24px;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .ch-hero { padding-top: 100px; }
    .ch-section { padding: 64px 0; }
  }
</style>
